{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2022-1669","published":"2022-05-25T11:03:48Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:17:54.837588Z","upstream":["CVE-2022-1355"],"summary":"libtiff security update","details":"This libtiff provides support for the Tag Image File Format (TIFF), a widely used format for storing image data. The latest version of the TIFF specification is available on-line in several different formats.And contains command-line programs for manipulating TIFF format image files using the libtiff library.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nA stack buffer overflow flaw was found in Libtiffs tiffcp.c in main() function. This flaw allows an attacker to pass a crafted TIFF file to the tiffcp tool, triggering a stack buffer overflow issue, possibly corrupting the memory, and causing a crash that leads to a denial of service.(CVE-2022-1355)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"libtiff","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/libtiff&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"4.1.0-11.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["libtiff-4.1.0-11.oe1.aarch64.rpm","libtiff-debuginfo-4.1.0-11.oe1.aarch64.rpm","libtiff-debugsource-4.1.0-11.oe1.aarch64.rpm","libtiff-devel-4.1.0-11.oe1.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["libtiff-help-4.1.0-11.oe1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["libtiff-4.1.0-11.oe1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["libtiff-4.1.0-11.oe1.x86_64.rpm","libtiff-debuginfo-4.1.0-11.oe1.x86_64.rpm","libtiff-debugsource-4.1.0-11.oe1.x86_64.rpm","libtiff-devel-4.1.0-11.oe1.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2022-1669.json"}},{"package":{"name":"libtiff","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP3","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/libtiff&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"4.1.0-11.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["libtiff-4.1.0-11.oe1.aarch64.rpm","libtiff-debuginfo-4.1.0-11.oe1.aarch64.rpm","libtiff-debugsource-4.1.0-11.